Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editAddPoly(25.10)                                          editAddPoly(25.10)

Name
       editAddPoly - Defines a vertex or corner of a polygon

Syntax
       editAddPoly

       [-help]

       <point>

       Defines  a  vertex  or  corner of a polygon. By issuing the editAddPoly
       command n times, you can create a polygon with n+1 sides. You can  then
       specify  the editCommitPoly command to end the polygon at the specified
       coordinates. editAddPoly honors the  setEditMode  -shape  option.  This
       means  if  you  want  to  create a polygon of a specific shape, you can
       first use setEditMode -shape to specify the required shape and then use
       editAddPoly and editCommitPoly to create the polygon.

       The editAddPoly command is DRC aware. When you create a  polygon  shape
       using this command, the tool marks any DRC violations in the shape dur-
       ing creation, provided that setEditMode -dcr_on is set to 1 (default).

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editAddPoly parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editAddPoly

       <point>
              Specifies  the  x  and y coordinates of a vertice or corner of a
              wire polygon.

Example
              * The following commands create three-sided  wire  polygon  that
                ends at the point specified by editCommitPoly.

                editAddPoly 700 300

                editAddPoly 700 500

                editCommitPoly 200 400

                The first side of the wire polygon starts at 700, 300 and ends
                at  700,  500.  The second side starts at 700, 500 and ends at
                200, 400. The third side is formed  by  joining  the  starting
                point  of the polygon (700,300) and the ending point specified
                by editCommitPoly (200,400).

